   <head>EPITAPH On Brigadier General HILL.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">manners gentle, yet a friend to truth,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">With age not peevish, nor yet vain in youth:</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Brave, yet humane, and blameless tho' severe;</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">His speech was open, and his heart sincere:</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">In courts unbrib'd, not factious tho' retir'd;</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Most lov'd the Soldier, more the Man admir'd.</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">A Queen his Mistress,. and his Friend, Mankind;</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">His Fortunes! — to yon little spot confin'd.</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Such once was  — and various tho' his lot,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The same Companion, favour'd, or forgot.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
